cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SD 

The paper proposes a new adaptive filtering algorithm that uses a generalized Gaussian kernel. This algorithm has applications in machine learning, computer vision, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Sound).
